  "texts": [
    "primarily on the excellence of the generated data, and secondarily on the efficiency of various recommendation models when leveraging the generated data in comparison to the initial data.In order to analyse variant and in-variant blur, Khan et al. [65] suggested a multi-scaled GAN trained with legacy images leveraging deep learning techniques.",
    "For the suggested GAN, various scaled visuals with associated gradients were combined to form a multichannel single input.",
    "To investigate important aspects in the bottleneck region and solve the vanishing gradient problem, residual-and dense-networks were coupled.",
    "Gradient-penalty hybrid content loss function was used to lessen the disparity between the generated and real-world photos.",
    "Structure sparsity may result in artefacts since some information may be lost in the output."
